Key Match Events: Kyle Schwarber and Weston Wilson each drove in two runs

Post-Match Reflections: Philadelphia finished 95-67, the second-best record in the National League behind the Los Angeles Dodgers (98-64)
The Phillies have a bye in the first round of the playoffs
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Phillies’ victory total was the team’s highest since winning 102 games in 2011 --- the last time they won the division
Others: Aaron Nola (14-8) allowed three runs in five-plus innings and struck out seven
Jake Irvin (10-14) allowed six runs and struck out three in 4 1/3 innings
